    <note>Qian(1) Guanfu [7143] His ancestors were members of a cadet branch of the Wuyue ruling family and were granted lands in Suzhou, Changshu xian where they settled. Yu(2)'s [7144] father, Xu(3) Duo's [7248] son-in-law, Chen(1) Danian's [7130] and Xu(3) Tingxian's [7247] father-in-law. He served as a Hubu langzhong for six months in 1138. His son, Dian [3038], received the jinshi degree in 1145 and served as Jiangxi yunfu in 1174 and was dismissed as Sinong qing in 1183. Qinchuan zhi, 8.13a, 14a; XNYL, 119.5b, 120.13b-14a, 124.3a; Liu Yizhi, WJ, 51.6b-11b, 18b-21a (wife, born Xu, who died in 1156 at age 59); Shengzheng, 53.15a; SHY:ZG, 72.8a; YLDD, 2368.5a. CBD, 5, 4089.</note>
